post_text: Five day meal distributions will continue to be served at all nine school sites including Nyeland Acres on Mondays between the hours of 12-2 p.m. For the safety of our community and staff, we will be offering a drive thru option for those parents who wish to pick up meals from their cars. Simply drive to your site, pull up in the designated drive up area and our staff will place the meals in your vehicle. There will be an alternate pickup area for those who wish to walk up to pick up meals. Please bring a cart if you need assistance transporting your meals. #rioschooldistrict #rioschools #feedingamerica #feedthechildren

post_text: Do you know what is the definition of tessellation and what does it take to create one? When a geometric shape is repeated over and over again, covering a plane of tiles without any gaps or overlaps, it results in a tessellation ‚Äì a mosaic pattern of a mesmerizing visual effect. This Tessellations art activity is inspired by the artist MC Escher and it works on drawing the principles of Design: pattern, repetition and unity. We hope you enjoy the lesson. #rioschools #rioschooldistrict

post_text: Elmer the Patchwork Elephant an art activity inspired by the children‚Äôs book by David McKee. Elmer is an elephant with rainbow and white squares arranged as a patchwork. He has a cheerful and optimistic personality, and he loves practical jokes. We will draw Elmer together we want you to focus on lines, shapes, and colors. The concept is that patterns are created through repetition of lines, shapes, colors. Hope you enjoy the lesson. #rioschools #rioschooldistrict

text: Rio School District will be keeping our schools closed at least through Friday May 1st. Our new target date to reopen is Monday, May 4th. Rio is strong. #rioschools #rioschooldistrict #coronavirus #coronavirusupdate

post_text: Today is our third day with schools closed due to the coronavirus event. This a letter from Rio School District Superintendent Dr. Puglisi to provide an update for our school community. Rio is strong. #rioschools #rioschooldistrict #coronavirus #coronavirusupdate

post_text:
Effective Wednesday, March 18, 2020 all district site offices will be closed. Our district office hours will be from 9:00 a.m to 12:00 p.m.

School lunches will continue to be served daily in the site cafeterias from 10:30 till 12:30.p.m.

Parents may call or come to the office to drop off or pick up enrollment packets. We encourage you to call prior to coming in to let us know you are coming. Please call us at 805-485-3111. #rioschools #rioschooldistrict
